**Code Explanation:**

The code performs a residual analysis on the test set to detect scale-dependent biases in the model's reconstruction. It first loads the test set indices from data/splits.json and initializes the CompSepDataset and the trained UNet model. For each patch in the test set, it computes the model's prediction and calculates the residual map as R = Truth - Reconstruction. The power spectra of both the residual (R_ell) and the ground truth (truth_ell) are computed using the utils.powers function. The mean power spectra across all test patches are then calculated, and the scale-dependent bias is defined as B(ell) = mean(R_ell) / mean(truth_ell). The bias values at specific multipoles (ell approx 1000, 3000, 5000, 8000) are printed to the console for quantitative evaluation. Finally, the script generates a 3-panel diagnostic plot showing: (1) the mean residual and truth power spectra as a function of ell, (2) the scale-dependent bias B(ell) as a function of ell, and (3) a 2D scatter plot of the residual power spectrum versus the truth power spectrum colored by ell. The computed statistics and the plot are saved to the data/ directory.

**Modifications:**

Added the required if __name__ == '__main__': block, ensured all paths point to the data/ directory, removed LaTeX rendering, and ensured all imports are correct.

